@startuml
skinparam linetype ortho
title Accounting Archetype - Model

' ===== CORE ACCOUNTING =====
package "Core Accounting" #E6F3FF {

  object Transaction
  object "Entry\n<<sealed>>" as Entry

  object AccountDebited
  object AccountCredited

  object Account
  object "AccountType\n<<enum>>" as AccountType
  object EntryAllocations
  object "TransactionEntriesConstraint\n<<interface>>" as TransactionEntriesConstraint

  object BALANCING_CONSTRAINT
  object MIN_2_ENTRIES_CONSTRAINT
  object MIN_2_ACCOUNTS_INVOLVED_CONSTRAINT

  Transaction "1" *--> "2..*" Entry
  Transaction --> TransactionEntriesConstraint

  BALANCING_CONSTRAINT --|> TransactionEntriesConstraint
  MIN_2_ENTRIES_CONSTRAINT --|> TransactionEntriesConstraint
  MIN_2_ACCOUNTS_INVOLVED_CONSTRAINT --|> TransactionEntriesConstraint

  AccountDebited --|> Entry
  AccountCredited --|> Entry

  Entry --> Account
  Account --> AccountType

  Entry ..> EntryAllocations : tracked by
}

' ===== TRANSACTION BUILDING =====
package "Transaction Building" #FFF4E6 {

  object TransactionBuilderFactory
  object TransactionBuilder

  TransactionBuilderFactory .down.> TransactionBuilder : creates
}

' ===== POSTING RULES =====
package "Posting Rules" #E8F5E9 {

  object "PostingRule\n<<interface>>" as PostingRule
  object ConfigurablePostingRule
  object PostingRuleExecutor

  ConfigurablePostingRule -up-|> PostingRule
  PostingRuleExecutor o-right-> PostingRule

  ' Hidden dla układu
  PostingRule -[hidden]down- ConfigurablePostingRule
}

' Relacje między pakietami
TransactionBuilder .down.> Transaction : builds
PostingRuleExecutor .up.> Transaction : generates

note right of Account
  **Account = konto księgowe**

  - NIE wie o właścicielach!
  - Tylko księgowanie (debit/credit)
  - Optimistic locking (version)
  - Events (DebitEntryRegistered, CreditEntryRegistered)

  Właściciele (Party, FleetCard, etc.)
  mają accountId - nie na odwrót!
end note

note right of Transaction
  **Transaction grupuje entries**

  - refId dla reversals/compensations
  - execute() dodaje entries do kont

  **TransactionEntriesConstraint:**
  - BALANCING_CONSTRAINT (Σ Debits = Σ Credits = 0)
  - MIN_2_ENTRIES_CONSTRAINT (minimum 2 entries)
  - MIN_2_ACCOUNTS_INVOLVED_CONSTRAINT (minimum 2 konta)
end note

note right of Entry
  **Entry = sealed interface**

  Dwie implementacje:
  - AccountDebited (amount negated)
  - AccountCredited (amount positive)

  appliedTo = alokacja do innego Entry
  validity = ważność zapisu
  metadata = dodatkowe dane
end note

note right of PostingRule
  **Posting Rule = automatyzacja**

  Na podstawie Transaction generuje
  dodatkowe Transactions

  eligibility → warunek kiedy reguła działa
  priority → kolejność wykonywania
end note

@enduml
